'''Budyonnivskyi District''' ({{lang-uk|Будьоннівський район}}) is an urban district of the city of [[Donetsk]], [[Ukraine]], named after [[Marshal of the Soviet Union]] [[Semyon Budyonny|Semyon Mikhailovich Budyonny]].
It was created in 1980 out of the Proletarskyi, Kirovskyi and Leninskyi districts. The district's name was a revival of the original name of Proletarskyi District.
