'''Eklenhui (Iyojwa'ja Chorote)''' is a language spoken in northeast [[Salta province]] in [[Argentina]] by 800. It is also known as Choroti, Yofuaha, and Eklenjuy.
It is distinct from the similarly named [[Iyo'wujwa Chorote]].
