Phonetic notes:
*{{IPAslink|p}} and {{IPAslink|v}} occur mostly in borrowings from Persian, and may be assimilated to {{IPA|/b/}} or {{IPA|/f/}} in some speakers. *{{IPA|/ɡ/}} is pronunciation of /{{IPA|q}}/ in Khuzestani Arabic and the rest of southern Mesopotamian dialects. *The gemination of the flap /ɾ/ results in a trill /r/.
