'''Religism''' is the tendency to believe in [[religious]] [[ideologies]] as opposed to [[Rationality|rational]] facts.
In many [[country|countries]] religism is preventing development towards a more modern society in either [[Human Development Index|material living conditions]] or [[human freedom]].
To the extreme religism can result in death by refusing a [[medical treatment]] to a patient because of religious beliefs.
Religism can also prevent people from choosing a loved partner or impede them access to a profession or an activity they would like to do.
Sometimes it also bars access to certain [[food]] types even in case of hunger.
Religism is often associated to an extreme grip of traditions and usually put a religion above rational thinking.

