{{Infobox language | name = Semaq Beri | altname = Semoq Beri | nativename = | states = [[Malaysia]] | region = [[Malay Peninsula]] | speakers = 2,500 | date = 2007 | ref = e18 | familycolor = Austroasiatic | fam2 = [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] | fam3 = [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern Aslian]] | fam4 = | iso3 = szc | glotto = sema1265 | glottorefname = Semaq Beri }}
'''Semaq Beri''' (Semoq Beri) is an [[Austroasiatic languages|Austroasiatic language]] spoken in the Malay Peninsula in the states of Pahang and Terengganu. It belongs to the [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern]] division of the [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] languages, along with [[Semelai language|Semelai]], [[Temoq language|Temoq]], and [[Mah Meri language|Mah Meri]]. A preliminary description of the Semaq Beri language by Nicole Kruspe was published in 2014.
